Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.record

Class PropertyRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.record.AbstractBaseRecord
      • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.record.PropertyRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<PropertyBlock>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RecordPropertyCursor
    public class PropertyRecord
extends AbstractBaseRecord
implements Iterable<PropertyBlock>
    PropertyRecord is a container for PropertyBlocks. PropertyRecords form a double linked list and each one holds one or more PropertyBlocks that are the actual property key/value pairs. Because PropertyBlocks are of variable length, a full PropertyRecord can be holding just one PropertyBlock.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Description copied from class: AbstractBaseRecord
        Clears this record to its initial state. Initializing this record with an initialize-method doesn't require clear the record first, either initialize or clear suffices. Subclasses, most specific subclasses only, implements this method by calling initialize with zero-like arguments.
